; Tests JVM spec requirement: interface cannot have multiple mutually exclusive flags
; Expected warnings: JVMS-001 (interface without abstract, interface with final/super/enum/module)
; This proves:
;   1. Parser detects interface without abstract flag
;   2. Parser detects all mutually exclusive flags (final, super, enum, module)
;   3. Multiple warnings are generated for a single class
;   4. Bytecode is still generated (warnings, not errors)

.class interface final super enum module EmptyClass
.super java/lang/Object

.class_end
